# Local config for the host vault scripts (scripts/install.sh, scripts/vault-compile.sh, etc).
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and set the values. Values are literal — use absolute paths,
# not ~ or $HOME. An explicit env var (or a systemd Environment=) overrides what's set here.
#
# This is separate from mcp/.env, which configures the MCP server.

# REQUIRED. Absolute path to the vault repo (inbox watched + compiled, wiki written).
KNOWLEDGE_REPO=/path/to/vault

# Optional. Path to the claude binary the vault jobs invoke (default ~/.local/bin/claude).
# CLAUDE_BIN=/home/you/.local/bin/claude

# Optional. Seconds between allowed manual compiles (default 3600).
# KNOWLEDGE_COMPILE_COOLDOWN=3600

# Optional. Scheduled-compile cadence — any systemd OnCalendar expression (default hourly).
# Applied by install.sh; re-run it after changing. The worker no-ops cheaply on an empty
# inbox, so a frequent cadence only does real work when there are captures. Examples:
# hourly | daily | weekly | *-*-* 03:00:00 | *-*-* *:00/30:00 (every 30 min).
# KNOWLEDGE_COMPILE_ONCALENDAR=hourly

# Optional. Synthesis cadence — the heavy whole-corpus /synthesize pass that reconciles drift
# and OPENS judgment-call GitHub issues. Keep it rare. Default 'Sun *-*-* 04:30:00 America/Detroit'
# (weekly, middle of the night, local time) to land on off-peak Claude Max capacity. Applied by
# install.sh. An optional trailing timezone needs systemd >= 250.
# KNOWLEDGE_SYNTHESIZE_ONCALENDAR=Sun *-*-* 04:30:00 America/Detroit

# Optional. Resolve cadence — the light /resolve pass that applies your answers on open issues
# and CLOSES them. Short-circuits cheaply when no issues are open. Default '*-*-* 03:30:00
# America/Detroit' (daily, middle of the night, local time), staggered an hour before synthesize
# so they don't collide on the shared lock. Applied by install.sh.
# KNOWLEDGE_RESOLVE_ONCALENDAR=*-*-* 03:30:00 America/Detroit

# gh auth (REQUIRED for synthesize/resolve, not compile): those two jobs run `gh issue ...`
# from inside their Claude run, so the host needs the GitHub CLI installed, on PATH, and
# authenticated — `gh auth login` once (stored in ~/.config/gh). compile never calls gh.

# Optional. Path to the shared lockfile all three vault jobs (compile/synthesize/resolve)
# acquire so they never run concurrently. Defaults to ~/.local/state/knowledge-tools/vault.lock.
# KNOWLEDGE_VAULT_LOCK=/home/you/.local/state/knowledge-tools/vault.lock
